owl:Ontology.terms:description: An application ontology for operating the Ocean Protein Portal.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: Ocean Protein Portal Ver. 2
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Ocean Protein Portal Ver. 2

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A link to a visual drawing of the conceputal model for a certain class
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: conceptualModel

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The conceptual model the describes this class can be found as an annotation of the following target class.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: describedinConceptualModelOf

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Frictionlessdata data type for a specific field (DataParameter) in a DataResource.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: frictionlessDataValueType

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Any constraints on the parameter values to help with processing a certain DataParameter. This property is used in the datapackage.json for describing a tabular-data-resource field.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: parameterValueConstraints

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines a delimiter to override the multipleValuedDefaultDelimiter for a certain DataParameter. This property is used in the datapackage.json for describing a tabular-data-resource field.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: parameterValueDelimiter

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A set of values for a DataParameter that specify that no data were recorded for that instance of an observation.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: parameterValueMissingValues

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The string of charactersin any template value of an IdentifierRegistryScheme or IdentifierRegistryService, encoded for regular expression, that could be replaced with the value of an Identifier's identifierValue.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: registrySchemeTemplateReplacementToken

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This metadata is about the specified Identifier
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: aboutIdentifier

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This Dataset is comprised of the following other DataResources.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: aggregatesDataFrom

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifer for which this information object annotates
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: annotatesIdentifier

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The dataset conforms to the Dataset Profile. Meaning to presents the profile's expected observations.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: conformsToProfile

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the type of Dataset or DataResource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: datasetType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The IdentifierScheme defined by some Thing. In the case fo the OPP, a single Dataset defines an IdentifierScheme for its local identifiers.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: definesIdentifierScheme

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This Specification is being defined for the following DataParameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: definesValuesForParameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A another DataResourceParameter which must exist in a DataResource for the DatasetProfile to be valid for a conforming Dataset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dependsOnParameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The identification that describes this amino acid
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describedByIdentification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The MetadataResource that describes this OPPDataset
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describedByMetadataResource

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The AminoAcidChain being described by this information.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describesAminoAcid

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The actual Peptide being described by this information.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describesPeptide

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The actual Protein being described by this Protien information.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describesProtein

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The ProteinIdentification suggested by the Peptide.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: forProteinIdentification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An AgentRole in which an Agent performs some Role on this particular Thing.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasAgentRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The size of the filter(s) being used during the sampling process. This could be a single value using schema:value property or a range of sizes using schema:minValue & schema:maxValue.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasFilterSize

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The score used to determine an amino acid's identification
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identificationBasedOnScore

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The score within a certain system for identifying an amino acid.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identificationScore

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An Identifier with a known IdentifierScheme for some Thing.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identifier

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An information record that annotated or further describes this Identifier.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identifierMetadata

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The scheme in which this Identifier has a unique value.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identifierScheme

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Role being performed by some Agent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: inRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The one, named or mutally agreed upon location at which Sampling occurred. This usually means a single coordinate at which sampling occurs depsite any variance in the location of the sensor at the time of measurement. This Station helps to normalize the intent of sampling at a certain location for cross-comparison between datasets.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: inVicinityOfStation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A DataResourceParameter that is included in a DataResourceParameterSet.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: includesDataParameterInSet

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Thing on/in which an Agent performs some Role.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isAgentRoleFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A DataResourceParameter that acts as a foreign key in some other, disjoint DataResource for the purpose of joining/linking data .
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isForeignKeyTo

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The thing being identified
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isIdentifierOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An Identifier that bleongs within this scheme.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isIdentifierSchemeFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An real-world instance of some conceptual thing.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isInstanceOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A Pathway for some Kegg Orthology entry.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: keggPathway

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The orthology for which this pathway belongs
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: keggPathwayForOrthology

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The NCBI Identifier for which this name describes.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: ncbiTaxonName

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An observation made about a single Sample for some identified amino acid.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: observationInSample

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The PeptideIdentification being asserted by the observer of some Sample.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: observedPeptide

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifier resolving service offered by an identifier registry's support for some identifier scheme
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: offersResolvingService

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The expected data type for all values of this DataResourceParameter. This helps the OPP understand how to process, visualize, and serialize these data.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameterDataType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A the DataResourceType for which this DataResourceParameter specifies.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameterInResourceType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The AgentRole which was performed by this Agent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: performedAgentRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Organization at which the acting Agent performed the Role
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: performedAtOrganization

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Agent acting in some Role.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: performedBy

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Agent for which the performing Agent is acting in a certain Role.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: performedOnBehalfOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A file type for which the OPP knows how to process for ingestion
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: processableFileType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The existence of some Thing provides the ability for some Agent to perform this Role.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: providesRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The IdentifierScheme for which this IdentifierRegistryScheme provides certain Identifier services for
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: providesServicesFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The DatasetProfile requires that at least one of the DataParameters described by this set of DataResourceParameters is required in the OPPDataset that conforms to the DatasetProfile.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: requiresOneParameterFromSet

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The identfier scheme at some registry for which this service resolves identifiers for.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: resolvesIdentifiersFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An AgentRole performing this specific Role
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: roleFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An observation made from a single Sample about an identified amino acid
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sampleAminoAcidProperty

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to the Cruise that hosted the Sampling Sensor
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sampleFromCruise

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An observation made from a single Sample about an identified peptide
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: samplePeptideProperty

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An observation made from a single Sample about an identified protein
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sampleProteinProperty

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Dataset for which this MetadataResource contains a metadata description of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serializesMetadataFor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A sample for which this Dataset stores observations results for.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: storesResultsForSample

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This peptide suggests that the following ProteinIdentification (linked via forProteinIdentification).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: suggestsProtein

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An IdentifierRegistry's interpretation of some IdentifierScheme through which thee registry offer's resolving services.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: supportsIdentifierSchemeWith

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The units that are expected for a certain DataParameter within a DataResource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: unitsReportedIn

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A DataResourceParameter for which the DatasetProfile specifies certain restrictions or expectations.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: usesDataResourceParameter

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: absolute units of a peptide or protein identification measured in fmol/liter
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: absoluteUnits

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name given to the amino acid being identified by some identifying agent.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: aminoAcidName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The amino acid chain, written as a string of characters, that identifies a specific amino acid.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: aminoAcidSequence

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that the related ProteinIdentification is the best identified protein.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: bestProtein

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The best SEQUEST DCn score
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: bestSEQUESTDCnScore

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The best SEQUEST XCorr score
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: bestSEQUESTXCorrScore

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Some label for a certain cruise on which an OPP Dataset was collected.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: cruiseID

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The depth in meters where some sample was collected.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: depth

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Thee probability of the correctness/confidence of the identification
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: identificationProbability

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The unique value in some IdentifierScheme
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: identifierValue

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name of some Entry in the Kegg Database. This could be thee name of an Orthology or Pathway, etc.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: keggName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
The Kegg Orthology Definition
Example: "nitrate reductase / nitrite oxidoreductase, alpha subunit [EC:1.7.5.1 1.7.99.-]" via `https://www.genome.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?K00370`
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: keggOrthologyDefinition

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The maximum size of the filter used during sampling. Measured in microns.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: maximumFilterSize

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The minimum size of a filter used during sampling. Mesaured in microns.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: minimumFilterSize

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A protein's molecular weight measured in kiloDaltons
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: molecularWeight

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: For a DataResourceParameter that can have multiple values (schema:multipleValues == TRUE), this is the default delimiter to be used for parsing DataResourceTypes that encode all values into one. One example might be tabular data where a cell contains multiple values separated by a semicolon.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: multiValuedDefaultDelimiter

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name of the parameter within the DataResource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: parameterNameInResource

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies whether a DatasetProfile recommends that a certain DataParameter exist in a DataResource. Recommendation doesn't mean its required, but rather it would be useful for data consumers.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: parameterValueRecommended

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A regex pattern defining how to find the portion of a property's value that should be used as it's actual value. Example": a mlecular weigght property with values that contain the units in the value like '255 kDa' could be processed to obtain the numeric value with a parameterValueRegexPattern defined as "([0-9.]+)\ kDa".
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: parameterValueRegexPattern

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The amino acid chain, written as a string of characters, that identifies a specific Peptide.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: peptideSequence

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The position in a DataResource could mean the column number in a tabular file or for FASTA files mean that the identfier = position #1 and the sequence = position #2.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: positionInDataResource

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A convenience property that is a proxy for opp:identifier => opp:DatasetProteinIdentifier => identifierValue
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proteinIdentifier

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name given to the protein being identified by some identifying agent.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proteinName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The amino acid chain, written as a string of characters, that identifies a specific Protein.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proteinSequence

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The observed spectral count for a single protein from a single sample
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proteinSpectralCount

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The unique prefix within an IdentifierRegistry for representing identifiers for the associated IdentifierScheme
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: registrySchemePrefix

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A template to be used for injecting an identifierValue from the associated IdentifierScheme into this IdentifierRegistry's registrySchemePrefix
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: registrySchemePrefixIdTemplate

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The URI that unqiuely identifies the associated IdentifierScheme within an IdentifierRegistry
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: registrySchemeURI

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The URL template at which you can inject an identifierValue from the associated IdentifierScheme into for resolving the Identifier.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: registrySchemeURLTemplate

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The value of some score using a scoring method to identify an amino acid.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: scoreValue

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name or label used in the OPP user interface to identify a OPPDataset. This is used for readability.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: shortName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The sum of the +2, +3, +4 spectra counts.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: spectralCountSum

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The start index
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: startIndex

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name of some Station.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: stationName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The stop index
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: stopIndex

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An abstract class for specifying a person, organization or software entity that performs some action acting in some predefined role.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An identifier for an Agent
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AgentIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An agent performing some Role over a certain period of time (which may be unbounded).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AgentRole

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actual amino acid. This is not to contain information that helps identify an amino acid, but represents the amino acid being identified. Any information here, should be shared by all other representations of the amino acid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AminoAcidChain

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An information object for storing data about an amino acid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AminoAcidIdentification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A property of some amino acid that was observed in a single Sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AminoAcidSampleObservation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The best/selected identification of a specific Protein based on information in a PeptideIdentification. This means that a PeptideIdentification may have multiple Proteins that it identifies but that one of those proteins has been selected (identifiedBy) as the best identification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BestProteinIdentification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The best SEQUEST DCn score for identifying an amino acid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BestSEQUESTDCnScore

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The best SEQUEST XCorr score for identifying an amino acid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BestSEQUESTXCorrScore

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A deployment of some seagoing vessel on which one or more scientific objectives are studied.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cruise

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A conceptual understanding of a particular parameter that could be observed/measured within some data resource. This parameter typically means to describe an observalbe or measurable "property" (or attribute) of some "entity" (or object) in relation to some "environment" using some "method". This conceptual description of a parameter helps to link across datasets that may report different units or other variances outside the scope of some "property of an entity in relation to an environment using some observational/measuring methodology".
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataParameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Dataset witha single resource at which the observations can be found.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataResource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A specification of how a DataParameter is expected to be in a DataResource in order for the DatResource to conform to a DatasetProfile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataResourceParameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A set of DataResourceParameter instances for the purpose of validating a DatasetProfile. This helps the DatasetProfile set requirements or a grouping a DataResourceeParameters such as saying at least one of the group is required.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataResourceParameterSet

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A single observed or measured property in a single DataResource. This property should be an instance of a DataParameter
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataResourceProperty

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A named type for which a DataResource can be labeled with for the sole purpose of conforming to a DatasetProfile. This is necessary becuase a DatasetProfile defines the DataParameters which must exist in a DataResource in order to properly conform.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataResourceType

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The identifierScheme for a singular OPP dataset. The dataset itself is the realm in which other identifiers such as Station names, protein names, etc. are unique (but that may not be unqiue acorss other OPP datasets). This helps ensure that identifiers in a Dataset are not automatically assumed to be equivalent to each other.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DatasetIdentifierScheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A DatasetProfile defines the type of observations to be expected.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DatasetProfile

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The identifier used to reference the protein across/within the Dataset.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DatasetProteinIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An EC identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EnzymeCommissionIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A certain type of file for which the OPP knows how to handle inn some way (ingestion, serialization for download, etc)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FileType

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The filter size in micons of the sampler.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FilterSize

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A JSON file conforming to the Frictionlessdata specification for describing data resources. This file is typically named 'datapackage.json'.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FrictionlessDataPackage

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The numerical score used to identified an Amino Acid using some scoring method.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentificationScore

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unique identifier attributeds to some thing within some realm or domain or scheme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Information about an identifier that helps comprehend, reuse, or contextualize the Thing being identified. This could be a non-unique label or description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentifierMetadata

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A registry at which certain identifier schemes can resolve identifiers and offers certain services or resources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentifierRegistry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An IndentifierRegistry's interpretation of a specific IdentifierScheme. This deescribes how a registry represents identifiers for the related scheme as URIs, URLs, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentifierRegistryScheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A service offered by an IdentifierRegistry for all identifiers of a certain IdentifierScheme
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentifierRegistryService

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A realm or domain in which a specific Identifier has a unqiue value from all the other possible Identifiers within that domain.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IdentifierScheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry in thee Kegg Database
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KeggDatabaseEntry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Kegg Dataset Entry Identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KeggDatabaseEntryIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Kegg Orthology entry from the Kegg database
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KeggOrthology

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Kegg Orthology Identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KeggOrthologyIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Kegg Orthology (KO) entry's pathway.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KeggPathway

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A file or other type of data resource that contains the metadata describing a OPPDataset
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MetadataResource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An NCBI Taxon identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NCBITaxonIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A dataset suitable for the Ocean Protein Portal
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OPPDataset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An identifier for an Organization
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OrganizationIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The PFams description for this Protein
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PFamsDescription

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A PFams identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PFamsIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A peptide identified in a sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Peptide

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An information object where a dataset can store observations about an identified peptide in a sample. These observations may vary across many datasets claiming to identify the same peptide, so this entity serves as a way to store these observations separate from other peptide identifiation observations while still allowing these PeptideIdentification objeect to describe the same, singular Peptide.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PeptideIdentification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The peptide suggests tthat the subsequent Protein was a possible identification. The best identified protein is specified by setting the bestProtein property to TRUE.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PeptideIdentifiedProtein

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Some property of a peptide identification that was observed in a single sample.
The sum of all spectra count.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PeptideSampleObservation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The total spectral count of some identified peptide from a single sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PeptideSpectralCountSum

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An identifier for a Person
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PersonIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The actual Protein being identified in datasets. This real-world Protein is identified by a single amino acid sequence regardless of variations across ProteinIdentifications that describe this same, single Protein
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Protein

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A protein identification made based on information of a peptide identification. This entity serves as an information object used within a Dataset to identify and describe an actual Protein. Where a Protein has a single amino acid sequence that will not vary across datasets submitted to the OPP, th ereported protien names, molecular weights, etc may slightly vary across these datasets. ProteinIdentification exists so that individual datasets can report their findings and remain separate from other ProteinIdentification while still describing the exact same Protein with the same amino acid sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProteinIdentification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A class of identifier schemes used to unqiuely identify proteins.

Kegg Orthology (KO) Entry => opp:keggEntry (schema:identifier) KO Definition => opp:keggDefinition (aka schema:description) KO Pathway => opp:keggPathwayNames (rdf:Bag of KO names)
Note since the order of the pathways (or KeggPathway Index isn't provided we don't use an rdf:Seq
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProteinIdentifierScheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Some property of a protein identification that was observed in a single sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProteinSampleObservation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The total spectral count of some identified protein from a single sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProteinTotalSpectralCount

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A certain status, or position, played by some Agent that qualifies/contextualizes the actions performed by that Agent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Role

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A generally agreed upon location at which sampling occurred. This agreement enables the comparison of collected data over different reference frames such as time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Station

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A proxy for any tabular data file. This is useful for software that can detect a certain DataResource as being tabular for ingestion or serialization.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TabularFileType

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Uniprot identifier
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UniprotIdentifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The units used to record some DataParameter in a DataResource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UnitOfMeasure

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Parameter Set: Peptide Spectral Count - Date Requirement

owl:NamedIndividual.schema:description: In the 'biopython' this parameter refers to the value at Bio.SeqIO.parse()->record.id
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DataResourceParameter_FASTA-ProteinIdentifier

owl:NamedIndividual.schema:description: In the 'biopython' this parameter refers to the value at Bio.SeqIO.parse()->record.seq
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DataResourceParameter_FASTA-ProteinSequence

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If multiple values exist, the Kegg Pathway, Definition and other Kegg metadata are ignored because there is currently no defineed way to structure that information to ensure it logically matches to the list of identifiers here.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DataResourceParameter_ProteinSpectralCount_KeggIdentifier
